        "header": "1Introduction",
        "images": [
            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2606.05972/2606.05972v1/x1.png",
                "caption": "Figure 1:Causal graphs provide a language for modeling mechanisms.\nPrior work studies real-world structures, using text to infer relations among real-world concepts or estimating how interventions on them (e.g., changing an author’s gender) affect model predictions. In contrast, we study the LLM-inference causal graph: a causal graph over LLM-perceived concepts that explains how the model maps text to prediction.",
                "position": 344
            }
        ]
